                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 font-semibold mb-4">What is Company Formation?</h2>

                  <img src="/images/images/what-is-company-formation.jpg" alt="What is Company Formation" class="w-full object-cover lg:rounded" style="height: 28em;" />

                <p class="mb-4 mt-4">
                    Once the reasons behind the importance of the startup company formation are known, then the next thing would be an understanding of what company formation is all about. In the simplest definition, company formation is the process of making what you are legally recognized in the eyes of the law as a business. It is not merely a thing of picking up a business name but a thing of the legal form of business, registering with the government authorities, and ensuring that your business is up to date even on the first day.
                </p>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    When you come up with a business, you have to determine the way your company will exist. What is it going to be limited liability company (LLP), corporation, or sole proprietorship? Every structure has its rules, tax implications, and advantages. As an illustration, an LLC protects against personal liability and presents a simple form of taxation, and a corporation can find it easier to attract investors. Selecting an appropriate business structure is a key aspect of establishing a business, and your structure can influence your business for years to come.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl text-gray-800 font-semibold mb-4 mt-4">Benefits of Proper Startup Company Formation</h2>

                <p class="mb-4">
